    "The computational complexity of action-outcomes becomes an issue for the consequentialist when we generalize problems of type c3, e.g., to account for n number of actions:",
    "c4: optimal plan of up to n distinct actions Input: Same as c3.",
    "Output: An action plan such that v is maximized over all 𝜑 ⊆ E, no a ∈ is identical to itself, and | | ≤ n.",
    "The time complexity of an exact algorithm that solves c4 while adhering to the CPO is O(2 n).",
    "In other words, there is no polynomial-time tractable procedure for consequential- ists who try to solve problems of type c4."
  ],
